32static const char ALPHABET[] = "0123456789ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ-. *$/+%";
33
34/**
35* These represent the encodings of characters, as patterns of wide and narrow bars.
36* The 9 least-significant bits of each int correspond to the pattern of wide and narrow,
37* with 1s representing "wide" and 0s representing narrow.
38*/
39static const int CHARACTER_ENCODINGS[] = {
40 0x034, 0x121, 0x061, 0x160, 0x031, 0x130, 0x070, 0x025, 0x124, 0x064, // 0-9
41 0x109, 0x049, 0x148, 0x019, 0x118, 0x058, 0x00D, 0x10C, 0x04C, 0x01C, // A-J
42 0x103, 0x043, 0x142, 0x013, 0x112, 0x052, 0x007, 0x106, 0x046, 0x016, // K-T
43 0x181, 0x0C1, 0x1C0, 0x091, 0x190, 0x0D0, 0x085, 0x184, 0x0C4, 0x094, // U-*
44 0x0A8, 0x0A2, 0x08A, 0x02A // $-%
45};
46
47static_assert(Size(ALPHABET) - 1 == Size(CHARACTER_ENCODINGS), "table size mismatch");
48
49static const int ASTERISK_ENCODING = CHARACTER_ENCODINGS[39];
50
51static void ToIntArray(int a, std::array<int, 9>& toReturn) {
52 for (int i = 0; i < 9; ++i) {
53 toReturn[i] = (a & (1 << (8 - i))) == 0 ? 1 : 2;
54 }
55}
56
57static std::string ToHexString(int c)
58{
59 const char* digits = "0123456789abcdef";
60 std::string val(4, '0');
61 val[1] = 'x';
62 val[2] = digits[(c >> 4) & 0xf];
63 val[3] = digits[c & 0xf];
64 return val;
65}
66
67static std::string TryToConvertToExtendedMode(const std::wstring& contents) {
68 size_t length = contents.length();
69 std::string extendedContent;
70 extendedContent.reserve(length * 2);
71
72 for (size_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
73 int character = contents[i];
74 switch (character) {
75 case '\0':
76 extendedContent.append("%U");
77 break;
78 case ' ':
79 case '-':
80 case '.':
81 extendedContent.push_back((char)character);
82 break;
83 case '@':
84 extendedContent.append("%V");
85 break;
86 case '`':
87 extendedContent.append("%W");
88 break;
89 default:
90 if (character > 0 && character < 27) {
91 extendedContent.push_back('$');
92 extendedContent.push_back((char)('A' + (character - 1)));
93 }
94 else if (character > 26 && character < ' ') {
95 extendedContent.push_back('%');
96 extendedContent.push_back((char)('A' + (character - 27)));
97 }
98 else if ((character > ' ' && character < '-') || character == '/' || character == ':') {
99 extendedContent.push_back('/');
100 extendedContent.push_back((char)('A' + (character - 33)));
101 }
102 else if (character > '/' && character < ':') {
103 extendedContent.push_back((char)('0' + (character - 48)));
104 }
105 else if (character > ':' && character < '@') {
106 extendedContent.push_back('%');
107 extendedContent.push_back((char)('F' + (character - 59)));
108 }
109 else if (character > '@' && character < '[') {
110 extendedContent.push_back((char)('A' + (character - 65)));
111 }
112 else if (character > 'Z' && character < '`') {
113 extendedContent.push_back('%');
114 extendedContent.push_back((char)('K' + (character - 91)));
115 }
116 else if (character > '`' && character < '{') {
117 extendedContent.push_back('+');
118 extendedContent.push_back((char)('A' + (character - 97)));
119 }
120 else if (character > 'z' && character < 128) {
121 extendedContent.push_back('%');
122 extendedContent.push_back((char)('P' + (character - 123)));
123 }
124 else {
125 throw std::invalid_argument("Requested content contains a non-encodable character: '" + ToHexString(character) + "'");
126 }
127 break;
128 }
129 }
130
131 return extendedContent;
132}
133
134BitMatrix
135Code39Writer::encode(const std::wstring& contents, int width, int height) const
136{
137 size_t length = contents.length();
138 if (length == 0) {
139 throw std::invalid_argument("Found empty contents");
140 }
141 if (length > 80) {
142 throw std::invalid_argument("Requested contents should be less than 80 digits long");
143 }
144
145 std::string extendedContent;
146 for (size_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
147 int indexInString = IndexOf(ALPHABET, contents[i]);
148 if (indexInString < 0) {
149 extendedContent = TryToConvertToExtendedMode(contents);
150 length = extendedContent.length();
151 if (length > 80) {
152 throw std::invalid_argument("Requested contents should be less than 80 digits long, but got " + std::to_string(length) + " (extended full ASCII mode)");
153 }
154 break;
155 }
156 }
157
158 if (extendedContent.empty()) {
159 extendedContent = TextEncoder::FromUnicode(contents, CharacterSet::ISO8859_1);
160 }
161
162 std::array<int, 9> widths = {};
163 size_t codeWidth = 24 + 1 + (13 * length);
164
165 std::vector<bool> result(codeWidth, false);
166 ToIntArray(ASTERISK_ENCODING, widths);
167 int pos = WriterHelper::AppendPattern(result, 0, widths, true);
168 std::array<int, 1> narrowWhite = { 1 };
169 pos += WriterHelper::AppendPattern(result, pos, narrowWhite, false);
170 //append next character to byte matrix
171 for (size_t i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
172 int indexInString = IndexOf(ALPHABET, extendedContent[i]);
173 ToIntArray(CHARACTER_ENCODINGS[indexInString], widths);
174 pos += WriterHelper::AppendPattern(result, pos, widths, true);
175 pos += WriterHelper::AppendPattern(result, pos, narrowWhite, false);
176 }
177 ToIntArray(ASTERISK_ENCODING, widths);
178 WriterHelper::AppendPattern(result, pos, widths, true);
179 return WriterHelper::RenderResult(result, width, height, _sidesMargin >= 0 ? _sidesMargin : 10);
180}
